annotationA: Methionine-R-sulfoxide reductase B1; Methionine-sulfoxide reductase that specifically reduces methionine (R)-sulfoxide back to methionine. While in many cases methionine oxidation is the result of random oxidation following oxidative stress, methionine oxidation is also a post- translational modification that takes place on specific residues. Acts as a regulator of actin assembly by reducing methionine (R)- sulfoxide mediated by Mical on actin thereby promoting filament repolymerization
annotationB: Pyrroline-5-carboxylate reductase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; proline biosynthetic process
